exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib search matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib search <query> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Cross-entity unified search: customers, worksites, persons, vehicles and keikkas in ONE flat ranked list. Client-side parallel fan-out over the per-entity searches — use this to resolve "who/what is X" without guessing the entity type.
  Auth: requires login (any authenticated user).

ARGUMENTS
  <query> STRING    Search string (required)

FLAGS
  --in STRING    Comma-separated subset of: customer,worksite,person,vehicle,keikka
  --limit NUMBER    Max hits per entity (default: 5)
  --my-companies BOOLEAN    Search across every company you belong to (customer/worksite/person)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --asiakas ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  { items: [{ entity, id, label, detail, <nativeIdField> }], nextCursor: null, count, errors: [{ entity, message }] }

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

NOTES
  - A failing/denied entity degrades gracefully into errors[] — exit 0 if at least one entity succeeded; if ALL fail, exits with the first failure's mapped code.
  - Ordering: prefix label matches first, then entity order customer→worksite→person→vehicle→keikka.
  - Each hit carries its native id field (asiakasId/tyomaaId/personId/vehicleId/keikkaId) for a follow-up \`ib <entity> get <id>\`.
  - No backend changes — works against current production.
  - --my-companies covers customer/worksite/person only; vehicle and keikka stay scoped to the active company.

EXAMPLES
  ib search kamppi
  ib search 0401234567 --in person,keikka
  ib search "Rudus" --in customer --limit 10
"
`;

