exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib vehicle list matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib vehicle list [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  List vehicles visible to the active company. ownerAsiakasId derived from JWT. Rows are self-describing (showInGrid/firstDate/lastDate/deletedTime). Default scope = non-deleted with no narrowing, so grid-hidden AND expired vehicles ARE included; only soft-deleted are excluded. Use the flags to narrow or to reveal deleted rows.
  Permissions: requires auth.page.vehicle.read.
  Timezone: dates interpreted in active company timezone (Europe/Helsinki).

FLAGS
  --limit NUMBER    Max rows (capped at 500) (default: 100)
  --deleted BOOLEAN    Include soft-deleted vehicles (default: excluded)
  --grid-only BOOLEAN    Only vehicles shown in the grid (showInGrid=1)
  --valid-on DATE    Only vehicles whose validity window covers this day (YYYY-MM-DD or today/yesterday/tomorrow)
  --type NUMBER    Only this vehicleTypeId (see \`ib vehicle types\`)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --asiakas ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ vehicleId, plate, name, type, typeName, capacity, showInGrid:boolean, firstDate:YYYY-MM-DD|null, lastDate:YYYY-MM-DD|null, deletedTime:ISO|null }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → check auth.page.vehicle.read
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

SEE ALSO
  ib vehicle types

EXAMPLES
  ib vehicle list
  ib vehicle list --pretty
  ib vehicle list --grid-only --valid-on today
  ib vehicle list --deleted
  ib vehicle list --type 1
"
`;

