exports[`Help snapshots — contract stability > help for ib worksite search matches snapshot 1`] = `
"USAGE
  ib worksite search <query> [flags]

DESCRIPTION
  Free-text worksite search (POST /api/tyomaa/search). The query full-text-matches the worksite name, ALL FOUR address lines (street / line 2 / postal code / city), driving instructions, memo, formatted address, worksite number AND the contact person's name / phone / email — so a street fragment like 'Mannerheimintie' finds the worksite. Scoped to the active company. Safe under --read-only (sent as a non-mutating meta request, so it does NOT trip the read-only lock or the acting-as write line).
  Permissions: requires auth.page.tyomaa.read.

ARGUMENTS
  <query> STRING    search string (required)

FLAGS
  --limit NUMBER    Max results (backend caps at 100) (default: 50)
  --my-companies BOOLEAN    Search across every company you belong to (customer/worksite/person)

GLOBAL FLAGS
  --endpoint URL  --request-id ID  --quiet  --verbose  --pretty  --json  --read-only  --asiakas ID

OUTPUT (JSON, stdout)
  ListEnvelope<{ tyomaaId, name, tyomaaNum, address, address2, postalCode, city, formattedAddress, coords:{lat,lng}|null, drivingInstructions, comment }>

ERRORS (stderr, exit non-zero)
  exit 2 (HTTP 401)  Token expired          → ib auth refresh
  exit 3 (HTTP 403)  Permission denied      → check auth.page.tyomaa.read
  exit 6 (HTTP 500)  Backend error          → retry with --verbose

EXAMPLES
  ib worksite search Mannerheimintie
  ib worksite search 'Jokiniementie 13' --limit 10
"
`;

